1ï¸âƒ£ Introduction

The Online Banking System is a Java-based application that simulates basic banking operations such as account creation, login authentication, deposit, withdrawal, and balance enquiry.
The project is developed using Core Java concepts, Swing GUI, JDBC, Multithreading, and Servlets.

The main objective of this project is to understand object-oriented programming, event-driven programming, and database connectivity in real-world applications.

2ï¸âƒ£ Objectives of the Project

To implement real-time banking operations

To apply OOP principles in Java

To design an interactive GUI using Swing

To store and retrieve data using MySQL

To ensure thread-safe transactions

To demonstrate event handling and processing

